1
00:00:25,692 --> 00:00:27,683
[gulls cry]

2
00:00:40,273 --> 00:00:43,037
- [gull cries]
- [dolphins yap]

3
00:00:57,891 --> 00:01:00,485
# <i>I'll tell you a tale</i>
<i>of the bottomless blue</i>

4
00:01:00,560 --> 00:01:03,495
# <i>And it's, hey</i>
<i>to the starboard, heave-ho</i>

5
00:01:03,563 --> 00:01:07,055
# <i>Look out, lad</i>
<i>a mermaid be waiting for you</i>

6
00:01:07,133 --> 00:01:09,863
# <i>In mysterious fathoms below</i>

7
00:01:09,936 --> 00:01:12,404
Isn't this great?
The salty sea air,

8
00:01:12,472 --> 00:01:15,373
- the wind blowing in your face.
- [barks]

9
00:01:15,442 --> 00:01:21,039
- A perfect day to be at sea.
- Oh, yes, delightful. [retches]

10
00:01:21,114 --> 00:01:24,208
A fine strong wind
and a following sea.

11
00:01:24,284 --> 00:01:27,583
King Triton must be
in a friendly type mood.

12
00:01:27,654 --> 00:01:31,351
- King Triton?
- Ruler of the Merpeople, lad.

13
00:01:31,424 --> 00:01:34,120
Thought every good sailor
knew about him.

14
00:01:34,194 --> 00:01:35,752
Merpeople.

15
00:01:35,829 --> 00:01:39,390
Eric, pay no attention
to this nautical nonsense.

16
00:01:39,466 --> 00:01:42,128
But it ain't nonsense. It's the truth.

17
00:01:42,202 --> 00:01:47,105
I'm tellin' ya! Down in the depths
of the ocean they live! Oh!

18
00:01:47,173 --> 00:01:48,162
Aah!

19
00:01:48,241 --> 00:01:51,938
# <i>In mysterious fathoms below</i> #

20
00:01:55,548 --> 00:01:57,539
[sighs]

21
00:03:26,306 --> 00:03:29,707
[fanfare of trumpets]

22
00:03:29,776 --> 00:03:29,876
[coughs] His Royal Highness,
King Triton!

23
00:03:29,911 --> 00:03:35,075
[coughs] His Royal Highness,
King Triton!

24
00:03:36,449 --> 00:03:38,440
[applause, cheering]

25
00:03:49,929 --> 00:03:53,194
And presenting the distinguished
court composer,

26
00:03:53,266 --> 00:03:57,100
Horatio Felonious Ignacious
Crustaceous Sebastian!

27
00:03:57,170 --> 00:03:59,104
[fanfare of kazoos]

28
00:03:59,172 --> 00:04:02,039
[applause]

29
00:04:02,108 --> 00:04:04,099
- [both whinny]
- Whoa!

30
00:04:04,177 --> 00:04:08,045
I'm really looking forward
to this performance, Sebastian.

31
00:04:08,114 --> 00:04:11,049
[chuckles] Your Majesty!

32
00:04:11,117 --> 00:04:15,417
This will be the finest concert
I have ever conducted.

33
00:04:15,488 --> 00:04:18,753
Your daughters,
they will be spectacular!

34
00:04:18,825 --> 00:04:21,555
- [whinnies]
- Yes.

35
00:04:21,628 --> 00:04:25,962
- Especially my little Ariel.
- Yes, yes.

36
00:04:26,032 --> 00:04:30,264
She has the most beautiful voice. Hmm?

37
00:04:30,336 --> 00:04:33,430
If only she'd show up
for rehearsals once in a while.

38
00:04:33,506 --> 00:04:37,067
- [orchestra tunes up]
- [applause]

39
00:04:59,232 --> 00:05:01,996
# <i>Ah, we are the daughters of Triton</i>

40
00:05:02,068 --> 00:05:05,265
# <i>Great father who loves us</i>
<i>and named us well</i>

41
00:05:05,338 --> 00:05:08,535
# <i>Aquata</i>

42
00:05:08,608 --> 00:05:11,202
# <i>Andrina</i>

43
00:05:11,277 --> 00:05:14,269
# <i>Arista, Attina</i>

44
00:05:14,347 --> 00:05:17,339
# <i>Adella, Alana</i>

45
00:05:17,417 --> 00:05:20,386
# <i>And then there is the</i>
<i>youngest in her musical debut</i>

46
00:05:20,453 --> 00:05:23,286
# <i>Our seventh little sister</i>
<i>We're presenting her to you</i>

47
00:05:23,356 --> 00:05:24,823
# <i>To sing a song Sebastian wrote</i>

48
00:05:24,891 --> 00:05:26,222
# <i>Her voice is like a bell</i>

49
00:05:26,292 --> 00:05:29,523
- # <i>She's our sister Ari...</i>
- [all gasp]

50
00:05:29,595 --> 00:05:34,157
- [gasps]
- Ariel!

51
00:05:38,404 --> 00:05:40,634
[male voice] Ariel, wait for me.

52
00:05:40,707 --> 00:05:43,505
Flounder, hurry up.

53
00:05:43,576 --> 00:05:47,512
[pants] You know I can't swim that fast.

54
00:05:47,580 --> 00:05:50,606
There it is.

55
00:05:50,683 --> 00:05:53,015
[Ariel] Isn't it fantastic?

56
00:05:53,086 --> 00:05:57,113
Yeah, sure. It's great.
Now let's get outta here.

57
00:05:57,190 --> 00:06:00,159
Oh! You're not getting
cold fins now, are you?

58
00:06:00,259 --> 00:06:03,228
Who, me? No way.

59
00:06:03,262 --> 00:06:07,323
It's just... It, uh...
It looks damp in there. Yeah.

60
00:06:07,400 --> 00:06:09,664
And I think I may be
coming down with something.

61
00:06:09,736 --> 00:06:13,502
Yeah, I got this cough. [coughs]

62
00:06:13,573 --> 00:06:16,098
[whispers] All right. I'm going inside.

63
00:06:16,175 --> 00:06:18,370
You can just stay here
and watch for sharks.

64
00:06:18,444 --> 00:06:19,536
OK.

65
00:06:19,612 --> 00:06:21,807
[whispering] Yeah, you go.
I'll stay and...

66
00:06:21,881 --> 00:06:24,873
What? Sharks? Ariel!

67
00:06:24,951 --> 00:06:29,149
[grunts]
Ariel, I can't... I mean...

68
00:06:29,222 --> 00:06:31,816
- Ariel, help!
- [laughs]

69
00:06:31,891 --> 00:06:34,758
- Oh, Flounder.
- [whispers] Ariel.

70
00:06:34,827 --> 00:06:37,694
Do you really think there
might be sharks around here?

71
00:06:37,764 --> 00:06:39,755
Flounder, don't be such a guppy.

72
00:06:39,832 --> 00:06:42,926
I'm not a guppy. [grunts]

73
00:06:44,270 --> 00:06:45,862
This is great.

74
00:06:45,938 --> 00:06:48,873
I mean, I really love this.

75
00:06:48,941 --> 00:06:53,742
Excitement, adventure, danger
lurking around every corner...

76
00:06:53,813 --> 00:06:57,249
[screams] Ariel!

77
00:06:57,316 --> 00:07:01,013
[grunts] Oh, are you OK?

78
00:07:01,120 --> 00:07:03,247
Yeah, sure. No problem. I'm OK.

79
00:07:03,289 --> 00:07:05,280
Shh!

80
00:07:10,096 --> 00:07:13,793
Oh, my gosh. Oh, my gosh!

81
00:07:13,866 --> 00:07:17,461
Have you ever seen anything so
wonderful in your entire life?

82
00:07:17,537 --> 00:07:21,234
Wow! Cool! But, uh, what is it?

83
00:07:21,307 --> 00:07:24,435
I don't know, but I bet Scuttle will.

84
00:07:24,510 --> 00:07:26,478
What was that?

85
00:07:26,546 --> 00:07:28,309
Did you hear something?

86
00:07:28,381 --> 00:07:30,747
Mmm? I wonder what this one is.

87
00:07:30,817 --> 00:07:33,945
- Ariel?
- Flounder, will you relax?

88
00:07:34,020 --> 00:07:36,284
Nothing is going to happen.

89
00:07:36,355 --> 00:07:38,380
- [growls]
- Shark!

90
00:07:38,458 --> 00:07:41,222
Shark! We're gonna die!

91
00:07:47,266 --> 00:07:50,030
[Flounder screams]

92
00:07:58,110 --> 00:07:59,805
Oh, no!

93
00:07:59,879 --> 00:08:02,507
[grunts]

94
00:08:04,484 --> 00:08:06,975
[Flounder screams]

95
00:08:21,267 --> 00:08:23,963
- [growls]
- [Flounder whimpers]

96
00:08:29,208 --> 00:08:31,802
You big bully! [blows raspberry]

97
00:08:31,878 --> 00:08:33,004
[gasps]

98
00:08:33,079 --> 00:08:34,068
[Ariel chuckles]

99
00:08:34,146 --> 00:08:36,137
Flounder, you really are a guppy.

100
00:08:36,215 --> 00:08:37,807
I am not.

101
00:08:40,286 --> 00:08:43,414
# <i>Hmm-hmm, fourteen hundred</i>
<i>and ninety-two</i>

102
00:08:43,489 --> 00:08:45,923
# <i>Dah-de-dum</i>
<i>Dee-do-do</i>

103
00:08:45,992 --> 00:08:48,483
# <i>Rum-dim-dim</i>
<i>Dee-do-dee-do</i> #

104
00:08:48,561 --> 00:08:51,086
- [Ariel] Scuttle!
- Whoa!

105
00:08:51,163 --> 00:08:54,894
Mermaid off the port bow!

106
00:08:54,967 --> 00:08:58,903
[shouts] Ariel, how you doin', kid?

107
00:08:58,971 --> 00:09:02,668
- Whoa, what a swim.
- Scuttle, look what we found.

108
00:09:02,742 --> 00:09:05,677
We were in this sunken ship,
and it was really creepy...

109
00:09:05,745 --> 00:09:09,078
Human stuff, huh? Hey, let me see.

110
00:09:12,652 --> 00:09:17,316
Oh! Oh! Look at this.

111
00:09:17,390 --> 00:09:20,826
Wow. This is special.
This is very, very unusual.

112
00:09:20,893 --> 00:09:24,920
- What? What is it?
- It's a dinglehopper.

113
00:09:24,997 --> 00:09:28,296
Humans use these little babies...

114
00:09:28,367 --> 00:09:30,335
to straighten their hair out.

115
00:09:30,403 --> 00:09:35,170
See? Just a little twirl here
and a yank there and violee...

116
00:09:35,241 --> 00:09:39,177
Ya got an aesthetically pleasing
configuration of hair

117
00:09:39,245 --> 00:09:41,338
that humans go nuts over.

118
00:09:41,414 --> 00:09:43,439
A dinglehopper.

119
00:09:43,516 --> 00:09:45,245
- What about that one?
- Ah!

120
00:09:45,318 --> 00:09:51,120
This I haven't seen in years.
This is wonderful!

121
00:09:51,190 --> 00:09:56,457
- A banded, bulbous snarfblatt.
- [both] Oh!

122
00:09:56,529 --> 00:10:01,762
The snarfblatt dates to prehistorical
times when humans used to sit around

123
00:10:01,834 --> 00:10:05,065
and stare at each other all day.

124
00:10:05,137 --> 00:10:07,105
Got very boring.

125
00:10:07,173 --> 00:10:11,701
So, they invented this
snarfblatt to make fine music.

126
00:10:11,777 --> 00:10:14,075
Allow me.

127
00:10:14,146 --> 00:10:15,636
- [Scuttle coughs]
- Music!

128
00:10:15,715 --> 00:10:18,013
- It's stuck!
- Oh, the concert!

129
00:10:18,084 --> 00:10:20,484
Oh, my gosh! My father's gonna kill me!

130
00:10:20,553 --> 00:10:21,918
The concert was today?

131
00:10:21,988 --> 00:10:24,218
You could make
a little planter out of it.

132
00:10:24,290 --> 00:10:27,623
I'm sorry! I've gotta go!
Thank you, Scuttle!

133
00:10:27,693 --> 00:10:29,251
Any time, sweetie!

134
00:10:29,328 --> 00:10:31,489
Any time.

135
00:10:45,344 --> 00:10:49,337
Yes, hurry home, Princess.

136
00:10:49,415 --> 00:10:54,819
We wouldn't want to miss old Daddy's
celebration, now, would we?

137
00:10:54,887 --> 00:10:59,517
Ha! Celebration, indeed. Oh, bah!

138
00:10:59,592 --> 00:11:04,586
In my day, we had fantastical feasts,

139
00:11:04,664 --> 00:11:08,896
- when I lived in the palace.
- [whimpers]

140
00:11:08,968 --> 00:11:10,094
[gulps]

141
00:11:10,169 --> 00:11:12,694
And now look at me.

142
00:11:12,772 --> 00:11:15,570
Wasted away to practically nothing.

143
00:11:15,641 --> 00:11:19,702
Banished and exiled
and practically starving,

144
00:11:19,779 --> 00:11:24,807
while he and his flimsy
fish folk celebrate.

145
00:11:24,884 --> 00:11:29,912
Well, I'll give 'em something
to celebrate soon enough.

146
00:11:29,989 --> 00:11:32,184
Flotsam! Jetsam!

147
00:11:32,258 --> 00:11:37,491
I want you to keep an extra close watch
on this pretty little daughter of his.

148
00:11:37,563 --> 00:11:42,626
She may be the key to Triton's undoing.

149
00:11:46,472 --> 00:11:50,533
I just don't know what we're
going to do with you, young lady.

150
00:11:50,609 --> 00:11:52,201
Daddy, I'm sorry. I just forgot.

151
00:11:52,278 --> 00:11:54,371
As a result of your careless behavior...

152
00:11:54,447 --> 00:11:56,278
Careless and reckless behavior!

153
00:11:56,348 --> 00:11:58,578
...the entire celebration was, uh...

154
00:11:58,651 --> 00:12:02,314
Well, it was ruined! That's all!
Completely destroyed!

155
00:12:02,388 --> 00:12:04,549
This concert was to be

156
00:12:04,623 --> 00:12:08,218
the pinnacle of my distinguished career.

157
00:12:08,294 --> 00:12:12,060
Now, thanks to you, I am the
laughingstock of the entire kingdom!

158
00:12:12,131 --> 00:12:13,723
But it wasn't her fault...

159
00:12:13,799 --> 00:12:17,462
Uh, well, first, uh,
the shark chased us.

160
00:12:17,536 --> 00:12:21,028
Yeah, yeah. And we tried to...
but we couldn't, and he...

161
00:12:21,107 --> 00:12:24,304
[growls] And... And we... Whoa!

162
00:12:24,376 --> 00:12:26,310
[sighs] And then we were safe.

163
00:12:26,378 --> 00:12:29,142
But then this seagull came,
and it was, "This is this..."

164
00:12:29,215 --> 00:12:30,876
Seagull?

165
00:12:30,950 --> 00:12:33,680
- [gasps]
- What? Oh!

166
00:12:33,753 --> 00:12:35,846
You went up to the surface again,
didn't you?

167
00:12:35,921 --> 00:12:38,389
- Didn't you?
- Nothing happened.

168
00:12:38,457 --> 00:12:42,689
Oh, Ariel, how many times
must we go through this?

169
00:12:42,762 --> 00:12:47,392
You could have been seen by one of those
barbarians, by one of those humans!

170
00:12:47,466 --> 00:12:50,026
- They're not barbarians.
- They are dangerous.

171
00:12:50,102 --> 00:12:54,095
Do you think I want to see my youngest
daughter snared by a fish-eater's hook?

172
00:12:54,173 --> 00:12:56,664
I'm 16 years old.
I'm not a child anymore.

173
00:12:56,742 --> 00:12:59,438
Don't you take that tone of voice
with me, young lady!

174
00:12:59,545 --> 00:13:02,946
As long as you live under my ocean,
you'll obey my rules!

175
00:13:02,982 --> 00:13:05,917
- If you would just listen...
- Not another word!

176
00:13:05,985 --> 00:13:10,388
And I am never... never to hear of you
going to the surface again!

177
00:13:10,456 --> 00:13:12,447
Is that clear?

178
00:13:17,663 --> 00:13:20,223
Hmph! Teenagers.

179
00:13:20,299 --> 00:13:22,597
They think they know everything.

180
00:13:22,668 --> 00:13:26,331
You give them an inch,
they swim all over you.

181
00:13:26,405 --> 00:13:30,398
Do you think I was too hard on her?

182
00:13:30,476 --> 00:13:32,603
Definitely not.

183
00:13:32,678 --> 00:13:37,741
Why, if Ariel was my daughter,
I'd show her who was boss.

184
00:13:37,817 --> 00:13:41,412
None of this flitting to the surface
and other such nonsense.

185
00:13:41,487 --> 00:13:44,354
No, sir. I'd keep her
under tight control.

186
00:13:44,423 --> 00:13:47,187
- You're right, Sebastian.
- Of course.

187
00:13:47,259 --> 00:13:49,921
Ariel needs constant supervision.

188
00:13:49,995 --> 00:13:52,759
Someone to watch over her,
to keep her out of trouble.

189
00:13:52,832 --> 00:13:53,924
All the time.

190
00:13:53,999 --> 00:13:56,661
And you are just the crab to do it.

191
00:13:58,003 --> 00:14:01,302
[Sebastian] How do I get myself
into these situations?

192
00:14:01,373 --> 00:14:03,364
I should be writing symphonies,

193
00:14:03,442 --> 00:14:07,105
not tagging along after
some headstrong teenager.

194
00:14:09,782 --> 00:14:14,276
Hmm? What is that girl up to?

195
00:14:17,656 --> 00:14:19,886
[Sebastian pants]

196
00:14:28,767 --> 00:14:30,428
[gasps]

197
00:14:42,882 --> 00:14:43,871
Huh?

198
00:14:50,723 --> 00:14:53,886
Ariel, are you OK?

199
00:14:53,959 --> 00:14:56,587
[Ariel] If only I could
make him understand.

200
00:14:56,662 --> 00:14:59,654
I just don't see things the way he does.

201
00:14:59,765 --> 00:15:03,929
I don't see how a world
that makes such wonderful things

202
00:15:03,969 --> 00:15:05,561
could be bad.

203
00:15:05,905 --> 00:15:10,274
# <i>Look at this stuff, isn't it neat</i>

204
00:15:10,342 --> 00:15:13,641
# <i>Wouldn't ya think</i>
<i>my collection's complete</i>

205
00:15:13,712 --> 00:15:16,875
# <i>Wouldn't ya think I'm the girl</i>

206
00:15:16,949 --> 00:15:20,385
# <i>The girl who has everything</i>

207
00:15:20,452 --> 00:15:23,717
# <i>Look at this trove, treasures untold</i>

208
00:15:23,789 --> 00:15:27,088
# <i>How many wonders</i>
<i>can one cavern hold?</i>

209
00:15:27,159 --> 00:15:29,821
# <i>Lookin' around here you'd think</i>

210
00:15:29,895 --> 00:15:33,194
# <i>Sure, she's got everything</i>

211
00:15:33,265 --> 00:15:37,065
# <i>I've got gadgets and gizmos aplenty</i>

212
00:15:37,136 --> 00:15:40,572
# <i>I've got whozits and whatzits galore</i>

213
00:15:40,639 --> 00:15:44,405
# <i>You want thingamabobs? I got 20</i>

214
00:15:44,476 --> 00:15:48,708
# <i>But who cares</i>
<i>No big deal</i>

215
00:15:48,781 --> 00:15:53,809
# <i>I want more</i>

216
00:15:55,654 --> 00:15:59,249
# <i>I wanna be where the people are</i>

217
00:15:59,325 --> 00:16:03,386
# <i>I wanna see</i>
<i>Wanna see 'em dancin'</i>

218
00:16:03,462 --> 00:16:05,623
# <i>Walkin' around on those...</i>

219
00:16:05,698 --> 00:16:07,188
What do ya call 'em?

220
00:16:07,266 --> 00:16:08,255
Oh, feet.

221
00:16:08,334 --> 00:16:10,268
- [giggles]
- [grunts]

222
00:16:10,336 --> 00:16:13,897
# <i>Flippin' your fins</i>
<i>you don't get too far</i>

223
00:16:13,973 --> 00:16:17,431
# <i>Legs are required for jumpin', dancin'</i>

224
00:16:17,509 --> 00:16:19,636
# <i>Strollin' along down a...</i>

225
00:16:19,712 --> 00:16:21,612
What's that word again?

226
00:16:21,680 --> 00:16:23,204
# <i>Street</i>

227
00:16:23,282 --> 00:16:27,946
# <i>Up where they walk</i>
<i>Up where they run</i>

228
00:16:28,020 --> 00:16:31,080
# <i>Up where they stay all day in the sun</i>

229
00:16:31,156 --> 00:16:34,956
# <i>Wanderin' free</i>
<i>Wish I could be</i>

230
00:16:35,027 --> 00:16:38,087
# <i>Part of that world</i>

231
00:16:38,163 --> 00:16:41,894
# <i>What would I give if I could live</i>

232
00:16:41,967 --> 00:16:44,299
- # <i>Out of these waters?</i>
- [gasps]

233
00:16:44,370 --> 00:16:47,737
# <i>What would I pay to spend a day</i>

234
00:16:47,806 --> 00:16:51,071
# <i>Warm on the sand?</i>

235
00:16:51,143 --> 00:16:54,078
# <i>Betcha on land they understand</i>

236
00:16:54,146 --> 00:16:58,708
