You haven't noticed, hmm?

468
00:33:18,696 --> 00:33:21,529
Oh, well, I...

469
00:33:21,599 --> 00:33:25,000
- Sebastian?
- Hmm?

470
00:33:26,037 --> 00:33:29,973
I know you've been
keeping something from me.

471
00:33:30,041 --> 00:33:33,272
[gulps] Keeping something?

472
00:33:33,344 --> 00:33:35,278
About Ariel?

473
00:33:38,416 --> 00:33:41,852
- Ariel?
- In love, hmm?

474
00:33:41,919 --> 00:33:47,448
[whimpers] I tried to stop her, sir!
She wouldn't listen!

475
00:33:47,525 --> 00:33:50,653
I told her to stay away from humans!
They are bad!

476
00:33:50,728 --> 00:33:55,461
- They are trouble!
- Humans? What about humans?

477
00:33:55,533 --> 00:33:59,094
Humans? [chuckles nervously]

478
00:33:59,203 --> 00:34:03,867
Who said anything about humans? [yelps]

479
00:34:03,908 --> 00:34:04,075
Flounder, why can't you just
tell me what this is all about?

480
00:34:04,110 --> 00:34:08,375
Flounder, why can't you just
tell me what this is all about?

481
00:34:08,446 --> 00:34:12,075
You'll see. It's a surprise.

482
00:34:12,150 --> 00:34:14,209
Oh, Flounder.

483
00:34:16,287 --> 00:34:18,278
Flounder, you're the best!

484
00:34:18,356 --> 00:34:22,918
It looks just like him.
It even has his eyes.

485
00:34:22,994 --> 00:34:28,057
[giggles] Why, Eric, run away with you?

486
00:34:28,132 --> 00:34:31,829
Oh, this is all so... so sudden.

487
00:34:31,903 --> 00:34:33,928
[laughs]

488
00:34:34,005 --> 00:34:35,165
[gasps]

489
00:34:35,239 --> 00:34:37,173
Daddy?

490
00:34:40,578 --> 00:34:44,571
I consider myself a reasonable merman.

491
00:34:44,649 --> 00:34:49,609
I set certain rules,
and I expect those rules to be obeyed.

492
00:34:49,687 --> 00:34:51,177
But, Dad, I...

493
00:34:51,255 --> 00:34:54,520
Is it true you rescued
a human from drowning?

494
00:34:54,592 --> 00:34:55,581
I had to...

495
00:34:55,660 --> 00:34:59,255
Contact between the human world
and the mer world is strictly forbidden.

496
00:34:59,363 --> 00:35:02,127
Ariel, you know that!
Everyone knows that.

497
00:35:02,166 --> 00:35:05,693
- He would have died.
- One less human to worry about.

498
00:35:05,770 --> 00:35:08,034
- You don't even know him.
- Know him?

499
00:35:08,106 --> 00:35:11,200
I don't have to know him!
They're all the same.

500
00:35:11,275 --> 00:35:13,709
Spineless, savage,
harpooning fish-eaters

501
00:35:13,778 --> 00:35:15,211
incapable of any feeling...

502
00:35:15,279 --> 00:35:18,214
Daddy, I love him! [gasps]

503
00:35:18,282 --> 00:35:22,548
No! Have you lost
your senses completely?

504
00:35:22,620 --> 00:35:24,554
He's a human. You're a mermaid.

505
00:35:24,622 --> 00:35:26,112
I don't care.

506
00:35:26,190 --> 00:35:30,320
So help me, Ariel,
I am going to get through to you.

507
00:35:30,394 --> 00:35:34,262
And if this is the only way, so be it!

508
00:35:36,968 --> 00:35:39,835
Daddy! No!

509
00:35:39,904 --> 00:35:42,498
No! Please!

510
00:35:42,573 --> 00:35:46,270
Daddy, stop! Daddy, stop it!

511
00:35:49,013 --> 00:35:51,208
Daddy, no!

512
00:36:00,992 --> 00:36:02,983
[Ariel sobs]

513
00:36:14,739 --> 00:36:16,673
Ariel, I...

514
00:36:16,741 --> 00:36:19,073
[sobs] Just go away.

515
00:36:37,428 --> 00:36:43,025
Poor child. Poor, sweet child.

516
00:36:43,100 --> 00:36:48,003
She has a very serious problem.

517
00:36:48,072 --> 00:36:51,405
If only there were
something we could do.

518
00:36:51,475 --> 00:36:54,410
But there is something.

519
00:36:54,478 --> 00:36:59,142
Who... Who are you?

520
00:36:59,217 --> 00:37:01,447
Don't be scared.

521
00:37:01,519 --> 00:37:04,750
We represent someone who can help you.

522
00:37:04,822 --> 00:37:09,919
Someone who can make
all your dreams come true.

523
00:37:09,994 --> 00:37:12,019
[both] Just imagine...

524
00:37:12,096 --> 00:37:14,087
You and your prince...

525
00:37:14,165 --> 00:37:17,692
Together forever.

526
00:37:17,768 --> 00:37:19,702
I don't understand.

527
00:37:19,770 --> 00:37:25,606
Ursula has great powers.

528
00:37:25,676 --> 00:37:29,635
[gasps] The sea witch?

529
00:37:29,714 --> 00:37:32,979
Why, that's... I couldn't possibly.

530
00:37:33,050 --> 00:37:36,110
No! Get out of here. Leave me alone!

531
00:37:36,187 --> 00:37:38,417
Suit yourself.

532
00:37:39,423 --> 00:37:42,722
It was only a suggestion.

533
00:37:52,336 --> 00:37:53,360
Wait.

534
00:37:53,437 --> 00:37:56,895
[both] Yes?

535
00:37:56,974 --> 00:38:01,274
- [sniffles] Poor Ariel.
- I didn't mean to tell.

536
00:38:01,379 --> 00:38:03,779
It was an accident. [mutters]

537
00:38:03,814 --> 00:38:06,908
Ariel? Where are you going?

538
00:38:06,984 --> 00:38:09,612
Ariel, what are you doing here
with this riffraff?

539
00:38:09,687 --> 00:38:11,587
I'm going to see Ursula.

540
00:38:11,656 --> 00:38:16,116
[gasps] Ariel, no! No!
She's a demon. She's a monster.

541
00:38:16,193 --> 00:38:19,492
Why don't you go tell my father?
You're good at that.

542
00:38:19,563 --> 00:38:24,364
But... But, I... Come on!

543
00:38:39,850 --> 00:38:41,511
This way.

544
00:38:49,927 --> 00:38:51,861
[creatures moan]

545
00:38:54,598 --> 00:38:57,931
[gasps, grunts]

546
00:38:58,002 --> 00:38:59,333
[pants]

547
00:38:59,403 --> 00:39:03,669
[Ursula] Come in. Come in, my child.

548
00:39:03,741 --> 00:39:08,974
We mustn't lurk in doorways. It's rude.

549
00:39:09,046 --> 00:39:13,005
One might question
your upbringing. [chuckles]

550
00:39:14,752 --> 00:39:17,585
Now, then, you're here

551
00:39:17,655 --> 00:39:22,615
because you have a thing for
this human, this prince fellow.

552
00:39:22,693 --> 00:39:28,290
Not that I blame you.
He is quite a catch, isn't he?

553
00:39:28,366 --> 00:39:30,891
Well, angelfish,

554
00:39:30,968 --> 00:39:35,837
the solution to your problem is simple.

555
00:39:35,906 --> 00:39:37,931
The only way to get what you want

556
00:39:38,008 --> 00:39:39,999
is to become a human yourself.

557
00:39:40,077 --> 00:39:43,205
[gasps] Can you do that?

558
00:39:44,782 --> 00:39:49,719
My dear, sweet child. That's what I do.

559
00:39:49,787 --> 00:39:51,812
It's what I live for.

560
00:39:51,889 --> 00:39:56,155
To help unfortunate merfolk,
like yourself,

561
00:39:56,227 --> 00:40:02,393
poor souls with no one else to turn to.

562
00:40:02,466 --> 00:40:05,958
# <i>I admit that in the past</i>
<i>I've been a nasty</i>

563
00:40:06,036 --> 00:40:09,699
# <i>They weren't kidding when</i>
<i>they called me, well, a witch</i>

564
00:40:09,774 --> 00:40:13,107
# <i>But you'll find that nowadays</i>
<i>I've mended all my ways</i>

565
00:40:13,177 --> 00:40:15,611
# <i>Repented, seen the light</i>
<i>and made a switch</i>

566
00:40:15,679 --> 00:40:18,011
True? Yes.

567
00:40:18,082 --> 00:40:21,882
# <i>And I fortunately know a little magic</i>

568
00:40:21,952 --> 00:40:25,080
# <i>It's a talent that</i>
<i>I always have possessed</i>

569
00:40:25,156 --> 00:40:28,648
# <i>And here lately, please don't</i>
<i>laugh, I use it on behalf</i>

570
00:40:28,726 --> 00:40:31,627
# <i>Of the miserable, lonely and depressed</i>

571
00:40:31,695 --> 00:40:33,925
Pathetic.

572
00:40:33,998 --> 00:40:37,092
# <i>Poor unfortunate souls</i>

573
00:40:37,168 --> 00:40:40,331
# <i>In pain, in need</i>

574
00:40:40,404 --> 00:40:41,962
# <i>This one longing to be thinner</i>

575
00:40:42,039 --> 00:40:43,529
# <i>That one wants to get the girl</i>

576
00:40:43,607 --> 00:40:46,701
# <i>And do I help them? Yes, indeed</i>

577
00:40:46,777 --> 00:40:52,647
# <i>Those poor, unfortunate souls</i>
<i>So sad, so true</i>

578
00:40:52,716 --> 00:40:54,308
# <i>They come flocking to my cauldron</i>

579
00:40:54,385 --> 00:40:55,943
# <i>Crying spells, Ursula, please</i>

580
00:40:56,020 --> 00:40:59,456
# <i>And I help them</i>
<i>Yes, I do</i>

581
00:40:59,557 --> 00:41:01,491
# <i>Now it's happened once or twice</i>

582
00:41:01,525 --> 00:41:03,652
# <i>Someone couldn't pay the price</i>

583
00:41:03,727 --> 00:41:08,824
# <i>And I'm afraid I had to</i>
<i>rake 'em across the coals</i>

584
00:41:08,899 --> 00:41:10,833
# <i>Yes, I've had the odd complaint</i>

585
00:41:10,901 --> 00:41:13,734
# <i>But on the whole I've been a saint</i>

586
00:41:13,804 --> 00:41:18,832
# <i>To those poor unfortunate souls</i> #

587
00:41:18,909 --> 00:41:20,934
Now, here's the deal.

588
00:41:21,011 --> 00:41:26,210
I will make you a potion that will
turn you into a human for three days.

589
00:41:26,283 --> 00:41:28,843
Got that? Three days.

590
00:41:28,919 --> 00:41:31,683
Now, listen, this is important.

591
00:41:31,755 --> 00:41:34,121
Before the sun sets on the third day,

592
00:41:34,191 --> 00:41:38,628
you've got to get dear old princie
to fall in love with you.

593
00:41:38,696 --> 00:41:41,597
That is, he's got to kiss you.

594
00:41:41,665 --> 00:41:47,126
Not just any kiss,
the kiss of true love.

595
00:41:47,204 --> 00:41:50,935
If he does kiss you before
the sun sets on the third day,

596
00:41:51,008 --> 00:41:55,001
you'll remain human permanently.

597
00:41:55,079 --> 00:41:58,571
But if he doesn't, you'll turn
back into a mermaid...

598
00:41:58,682 --> 00:42:02,743
and... you belong to me!

599
00:42:02,786 --> 00:42:05,619
No, Ariel! [muffled]

600
00:42:05,689 --> 00:42:08,055
Have we got a deal?

601
00:42:08,125 --> 00:42:10,389
If I become human,

602
00:42:10,461 --> 00:42:13,225
I'll never be with
my father or sisters again.

603
00:42:13,297 --> 00:42:15,595
That's right!

604
00:42:15,666 --> 00:42:18,931
But you'll have your man.

605
00:42:19,003 --> 00:42:24,373
[chuckles] Life's full of
tough choices, isn't it?

606
00:42:24,441 --> 00:42:26,238
[cackles]

607
00:42:26,310 --> 00:42:30,576
Oh! And there is one more thing.

608
00:42:30,648 --> 00:42:33,208
We haven't discussed
the subject of payment.

609
00:42:33,284 --> 00:42:35,309
You can't get something for nothing.

610
00:42:35,386 --> 00:42:37,820
- But I don't have any...
- I'm not asking much.

611
00:42:37,888 --> 00:42:42,086
Just a token really, a trifle.
You'll never even miss it.

612
00:42:42,159 --> 00:42:46,596
What I want from you is... your voice.

613
00:42:46,664 --> 00:42:50,794
- My voice?
- You've got it, sweetcakes.

614
00:42:50,868 --> 00:42:54,497
No more talking, singing. Zip!

615
00:42:54,572 --> 00:42:56,563
But without my voice, how can I...

616
00:42:56,640 --> 00:43:00,508
You'll have your looks,
your pretty face.

617
00:43:00,611 --> 00:43:05,639
And don't underestimate the
importance of body language!

618
00:43:05,683 --> 00:43:06,672
Ha!

619
00:43:06,750 --> 00:43:09,651
# <i>The men up there</i>
<i>don't like a lot of blabber</i>

620
00:43:09,720 --> 00:43:12,280
# <i>They think a girl</i>
<i>who gossips is a bore</i>

621
00:43:12,356 --> 00:43:15,052
# <i>Yes, on land it's much preferred</i>
<i>for ladies not to say a word</i>

622
00:43:15,125 --> 00:43:17,457
# <i>And, after all, dear</i>
<i>What is idle prattle for?</i>

623
00:43:17,528 --> 00:43:18,961
Come on!

624
00:43:19,029 --> 00:43:21,896
# <i>They're not all that</i>
<i>impressed with conversation</i>

625
00:43:21,966 --> 00:43:24,594
# <i>True gentlemen avoid it when they can</i>

626
00:43:24,668 --> 00:43:26,192
# <i>But they dote and swoon and fawn</i>

627
00:43:26,270 --> 00:43:27,862
# <i>On a lady who's withdrawn</i>

628
00:43:27,938 --> 00:43:30,304
# <i>It's she who holds her tongue</i>
<i>who gets her man</i>

629
00:43:30,374 --> 00:43:34,208
# <i>Come on, you poor unfortunate soul</i>

630
00:43:34,278 --> 00:43:37,247
# <i>Go ahead, make your choice</i>

631
00:43:37,314 --> 00:43:40,841
# <i>I'm a very busy woman</i>
<i>and I haven't got all day</i>

632
00:43:40,918 --> 00:43:43,250
# <i>It won't cost much, just your voice</i>

633
00:43:43,320 --> 00:43:45,618
# <i>Ya poor, unfortunate soul</i>

634
00:43:45,689 --> 00:43:48,590
# <i>It's sad, but true</i>

635
00:43:48,659 --> 00:43:51,150
# <i>If you want to cross a bridge,</i>
<i>my sweet you've got to pay the toll</i>

636
00:43:51,228 --> 00:43:54,493
# <i>Take a gulp and take a breath</i>
<i>and go ahead and sign the scroll</i>

637
00:43:54,565 --> 00:43:56,795
# <i>Flotsam, Jetsam</i>
<i>Now I've got her, boys</i>

638
00:43:56,867 --> 00:44:00,633
# <i>The boss is on a roll</i>

639
00:44:00,738 --> 00:44:03,764
# <i>This poor, unfortunate</i>

640
00:44:03,807 --> 00:44:09,302
# <i>Soul</i>

641
00:44:10,814 --> 00:44:13,248
# <i>Beluga, sevruga</i>

642
00:44:13,317 --> 00:44:16,912
# <i>Come, winds of the Caspian Sea</i>

643
00:44:16,987 --> 00:44:20,616
# <i>Larynxis, glossitis</i>
<i>Et max laryngitis</i>

644
00:44:20,691 --> 00:44:24,183
# <i>La voce to me</i>

645
00:44:24,261 --> 00:44:26,593
Now, sing!

646
00:44:26,664 --> 00:44:30,930
[vocalizes]

647
00:44:32,169 --> 00:44:34,160
Keep singing!

648
00:44:45,616 --> 00:44:47,607
[vocalizing continues]

649
00:44:50,521 --> 00:44:53,388
[cackles]

650
00:45:21,952 --> 00:45:23,943
[pipe plays]

651
00:45:31,261 --> 00:45:32,751
[barks]

652
00:45:34,798 --> 00:45:39,792
That voice.
I can't get it out of my head.

653
00:45:39,870 --> 00:45:43,829
I've looked everywhere, Max.
Where could she be?

654
00:46:02,726 --> 00:46:07,686
Well, look at what
the catfish dragged in.

655
00:46:07,765 --> 00:46:10,393
[laughs] Look at ya. Look at ya.

656
00:46:10,467 --> 00:46:13,766
There's somethin' different.
Don't tell me.

657
00:46:13,837 --> 00:46:16,567
I got it. It's your hairdo, right?

658
00:46:16,640 --> 00:46:18,699
You've been usin' the dinglehopper?

659
00:46:20,277 --> 00:46:22,768
No? No, huh? Well, let me see.

660
00:46:22,846 --> 00:46:25,781
New seashells?

661
00:46:25,849 --> 00:46:28,317
No new seashells.

662
00:46:28,385 --> 00:46:30,945
I gotta admit I can't
put my foot on it right now.

663
00:46:31,021 --> 00:46:32,579
If I stand here long enough...

664
00:46:32,656 --> 00:46:34,089
She's got legs, you idiot!

665
00:46:34,158 --> 00:46:38,561
She traded her voice to the sea
witch and got legs. Geez, man!

666
00:46:38,629 --> 00:46:40,119
I knew that.

667
00:46:40,197 --> 00:46:42,131
Ariel's been turned into a human.

668
00:46:42,199 --> 00:46:46,499
She's gotta make the prince fall in love
with her, and he's gotta kiss her.

669
00:46:46,570 --> 00:46:50,301
[Sebastian]
And she's only got three days!

670
00:46:50,374 --> 00:46:53,309
Just look at her!

671
00:46:53,377 --> 00:46:56,312
On legs! On human legs!

672
00:46:56,380 --> 00:47:00,817
My nerves are shot!
This is a catastrophe!

673
00:47:00,918 --> 00:47:03,887
What would her father say?
I'll tell you what her father'd say.

674
00:47:03,921 --> 00:47:07,186
He'd say he's gonna kill himself a crab!
That's what he'd say!

675
00:47:07,257 --> 00:47:10,158
I'm gonna march meself
straight home right now

676
00:47:10,227 --> 00:47:12,821
and tell him just like I should
have done the minute...

677
00:47:12,896 --> 00:47:16,354
And don't you shake your head
at me, young lady.

678
00:47:16,433 --> 00:47:18,458
Maybe there's still time.

679
00:47:18,535 --> 00:47:21,265
If we could get that witch
to give you back your voice,

680
00:47:21,338 --> 00:47:24,830
you could go home with all
the normal fish and just be...

681
00:47:24,908 --> 00:47:28,435
Just be...

682
00:47:28,512 --> 00:47:33,745
Just be miserable
for the rest of your life.

683
00:47:35,786 --> 00:47:38,846
All right, all right.

684
00:47:38,922 --> 00:47:42,949
I'll try to help ya find that prince.

685
00:47:45,095 --> 00:47:50,055
Boy, what a soft shell
I'm turning out to be.

686
00:47:50,133 --> 00:47:52,158
Now, Ariel, I'm telling ya.

687
00:47:52,236 --> 00:47:56,319
If you wanna be a human, the first thing
to do is dress like one. Let me see.

688
00:47:58,989 --> 00:48:02,584
[sniffs]

689
00:48:02,659 --> 00:48:06,356
- [barks]
- Max? What?

690
00:48:06,429 --> 00:48:09,227
Huh? What? Max!

691
00:48:10,467 --> 00:48:13,800
[wolf whistles] Ya look great, kid.

692
00:48:13,870 --> 00:48:17,806
- Ya look sensational.
- [barks]

693
00:48:17,874 --> 00:48:18,863
[gasps]

694
00:48:18,942 --> 00:48:22,605
- [pants]
- [Sebastian mutters]

695
00:48:22,679 --> 00:48:24,670
[barks]

696
00:48:28,385 --> 00:48:31,252
[Eric] Max!

697
00:48:31,321 --> 00:48:32,845
Max!

698
00:48:32,923 --> 00:48:35,448
- Quiet, Max.
- [barks]

699
00:48:35,525 --> 00:48:38,085
What's gotten into you, fella? Oh.

700
00:48:38,161 --> 00:48:41,790
- Oh, I see.
- [barks]

701
00:48:41,865 --> 00:48:44,959
[Eric] Are you OK, miss?

702
00:48:45,035 --> 00:48:47,367
I'm sorry if this knucklehead
scared you.

703
00:48:47,437 --> 00:48:49,632
He's harmless really, uh...

704
00:48:51,641 --> 00:48:56,442
You seem very familiar to me.
Have we met?

705
00:48:56,513 --> 00:48:59,038
[Max barks]

706
00:48:59,115 --> 00:49:00,946
We have met. I knew it.

707
